I feel like i lost who i used to be, and i miss that fearless person who actually knew what they were doing. 21 and still dealing with anxiety makes me feel sorta bad that i haven't kicked it yet.. ANYWAYSSS i like this song .

snippet.textDisplay: The original was great, but this shit takes it to a new level. This pays respect and instills hope that punk/hardcore/post hardcore/metal isn’t dead. This is like reminiscing from 2000-2012. The golden years of warped tour/heavy/heartfelt music, jams past rock and hard rock of the 80s-90s. The “punk/SxE/scene/emo” (all different, but yet the same) times in the early 2000s had some of the hardest hitting lyrical masterpieces. From religion to partying. Anthems. The pioneers of this genre have disappeared, and 90%+ of new stuff isn’t worth a second listen. I appreciate this.
snippet.textOriginal: The original was great, but this shit takes it to a new level. This pays respect and instills hope that punk/hardcore/post hardcore/metal isn’t dead. The “punk/SxE/scene/emo” (all different, but yet the same) times in the early 2000s had some of the hardest hitting lyrical masterpieces. From religion to partying. Anthems.
